09/12/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu has told political leaders he plans to announce the name of the new prime minister Wednesday (December 10th), according to media reports.
Monday evening, the president held a new round of cabinet-formation talks with the main political parties, following general elections on November 30th.
Meanwhile, at a meeting earlier Monday, the Social Democratic Party (PSD) officially announced it would start negotiations with the election-winning Liberal Democratic Party to form a government majority.
Previous reports suggested the PSD was planning an alliance with the ruling National Liberal Party.
(Evenimentul Zilei, Gandul, Cotidianul, Nine O'clock - 09/12/08;
Mediafax, Agerpres, Hotnews, Reuters - 08/12/08)
